        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "This method is actually unusable.\n\n\nline 144 : Notice: Undefined index: coumn_name\n-> misspelled array key\n\nline 170 : array value of 'PRIMARY' key is buggy.\n-> after first set, $is_primary keeps its value during iteration (Must be reset for each iteration).\n\n\nbugs already reported in ZF-1092\nline 152 : Notice: Undefined offset: 1\n-> explode() doesn't always return a 2-dim array, so $rest can't be always set ($rest is useless here).\n\nline 154 : Warning: array_key_exists() The second argument should be either an array or an object\n-> wrong parameters order\n\n\nThe patch submitted correct all these bugs\n + bug ZF-1271 (switch to numeric indices)\n + little improvement : define values for 'COLUMN_POSITION' and 'PRIMARY_POSITION' keys\n\ntested on MSSQL Server 2000\n\n(Columns order seems to be the same for MSSQL Server 2005, according to http:\/\/msdn2.microsoft.com\/en-us\/library\/ms189813.aspx and http:\/\/msdn2.microsoft.com\/en-us\/library\/ms176077.aspx )\n"
        },
