            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/14510",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Thanks very much Marc for the patch!\n\nI have committed changes in revision 4757 including this patch, or very similar code.\n\nUnfortunately, I still do not have a MS SQL Server instance against which to test.  I'll leave this issue open until I can run the unit tests and verify the fix.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-05-07T17:59:45.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-05-07T17:59:45.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/14517",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mholzwarth",
                        "name": "mholzwarth",
                        "displayName": "Marc Holzwarth",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Bill,\n\nI have updated my working copy to revision 4757, thanks.\n\nBut you have forgotten a bug line 153 :\n\n{code}\/** Wrong code *\/\n$isPrimary = array_key_exists($primaryKeyColumn, $row[$column_name]);{code}\n\n-> the arguments should be switched (array_key_exists ( mixed key, array search )).\n\n{code}$isPrimary = array_key_exists($row[$column_name], $primaryKeyColumn);{code}\n\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mholzwarth",
                        "name": "mholzwarth",
                        "displayName": "Marc Holzwarth",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-05-08T06:35:03.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-05-08T06:35:03.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/14528",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Ok thank you I have applied that fix in revision 4764.  I'm sorry I can test only with \"php -l\" at this time.  :-(\nBut I hope to improve that this week.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-05-08T13:13:23.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-05-08T13:13:23.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/14532",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mholzwarth",
                        "name": "mholzwarth",
                        "displayName": "Marc Holzwarth",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Back to work, I have tested the revision 4764 on our sql server instance and discover a new bug that was not in my patch.\n\nYou have forgotten a line in my patch (probably not included after your correction on $primaryPosition) :\n{code}+        $column_position = 16;{code}\n\nThis var is used in the metadata array $desc :\n{code}\n            $desc[$row[$column_name]] = array(\n                'SCHEMA_NAME'      => null, \/\/ @todo\n                'TABLE_NAME'       => $row[$table_name],\n                'COLUMN_NAME'      => $row[$column_name],\n                'COLUMN_POSITION'  => (int) $row[$column_position],\n...\n{code}\n\nThat was a little improvement in my patch (the previous 'COLUMN_POSITION'  value was set to null (@todo).)\nOr maybe this improvement is not a good implementation too ?\n\n(Sorry for the inconvenience, I did only a visual check yesterday.)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mholzwarth",
                        "name": "mholzwarth",
                        "displayName": "Marc Holzwarth",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-05-09T03:18:51.000+0000",
